```

## Quality Checklist

Before delivering a summary, verify:
- [ ] **Accurate:** Does it faithfully represent the source?
- [ ] **Complete:** Are all essential points included?
- [ ] **Concise:** Is every word necessary?
- [ ] **Clear:** Would someone unfamiliar understand it?
- [ ] **Objective:** Is it free from added interpretation?
- [ ] **Structured:** Is it logically organized?

## Common Pitfalls to Avoid

❌ **Copying verbatim** - Summarize in your own words
❌ **Adding information** - Only include what's in the source
❌ **Losing nuance** - Preserve important qualifications
❌ **Burying the lead** - Put the most important info first
❌ **Being too vague** - Include specific details that matter
❌ **Ignoring context** - Note when context is essential to meaning

## Handling Special Cases

### When the source is unclear
- Summarize what IS clear
- Note areas of ambiguity
- Don't guess at meaning

### When the source is biased
- Summarize the content objectively
- Note the perspective/bias if relevant
- Don't correct or counter the bias in the summary

### When the source is very long
- Break into sections
- Summarize each section
- Provide an overall summary
- Offer to go deeper on specific sections

### When the source is technical
- Maintain technical accuracy
- Define key terms if needed
- Don't oversimplify to the point of inaccuracy

